This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on improving model robustness against spatial transformation-based attacks. It also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a joint adversarial training method for improving model performance. Additionally, it involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with the generation of adversarial attacks. The paper also discusses the security and cryptography (cs.CR) aspect of the problem as it deals with adversarial attacks. Finally, it involves neural networks (cs.NE) as it proposes a method for training neural networks to be more robust against attacks.
